e tools will function like real-time national accounts. In our 芒聙聹Canaries in the Coal Mine芒聙聺 work with ADP, we already see early-career workers in AI-exposed occupations experiencing weaker employment and earnings outcomes; in 2026, similar indicators will be updated monthly, not years later. Executives will check AI exposure metrics daily alongside revenue dashboards, and policymakers will use them to target training, safety nets, and innovation policy. The debate [...] Skip to content\\\\n\\\\n this year.\\\\n\\\\nBut additionally, AI sovereignty will gain huge steam this year as countries try to show their independence from the AI providers and from the United States芒聙聶 political system. What is AI sovereignty? In one model of sovereignty, a country might build its own large LLM. In another example, a country might run someone else芒聙聶s LLM on their own GPUs so that they can make sure their data doesn芒聙聶t leave their country. The term 芒聙聹sovereignty芒聙聺 isn芒聙聶t well defined, and HAI is currently working on a project to help people understand these different models and provide some analysis. [...] In 2026, I expect more focus on the archeology of the high-performing neural nets. We just published a paper on this called 芒聙聹Paying attention to attention in proteins.芒聙聺 I芒聙聶m seeing people using things called sparse autoencoders on the deep network to try to identify the features in the data that are driving performance. In science, there芒聙聶s an absolute mandate to open AI芒聙聶s black box, and I芒聙聶m starting to see us open that box.\\\", \\\"score\\\": 0.28678355, \\\"raw_content\\\": null}], \\\"response_time\\\": 5.98, \\\"request_id\\\": \\\"142becdc-9011-4bce-aa5c-da59ab82407d\\\"}\", \"tool_name\": \"web_search\"}",
