agents.\\\\n\\\\nBy deploying AI agents, organizations can streamline business processes, reduce manual errors, and gain a significant competitive advantage.\\\\n\\\\nAs agent technology matures, companies are increasingly integrating AI agents into multi-agent systems, where multiple ai agents collaborate to solve problems and execute tasks that would be too complex for a single agent or human agent alone. [...] ###### Key takeaways\\\\n\\\\n   AI agents are shifting from simple automation to autonomous digital coworkers, with 80% of enterprise apps expected to embed agents by 2026.\\\\n   Businesses are rapidly adopting agentic AI, driving 46%+ CAGR growth and delivering major gains in productivity, cost reduction, and decision-making speed.\\\\n   Multi-agent systems and deeper platform integrations are enabling agents to coordinate complex workflows across sales, support, supply chain, and finance.\\\\n   Low-code platforms, stronger cybersecurity agents, and responsible governance models are making AI agents faster to deploy, safer, and more scalable across the enterprise.\\\\n\\\\nAI agents are no longer an experimental side project inside enterprises; they芒聙聶re quickly becoming part of the core operating fabric.\\\", \\\"score\\\": 0.9999745, \\\"raw_content\\\": null}, {\\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.grandviewresearch.com/horizon/outlook/ai-agents-market/united-states\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"US Ai Agents Market Size \u0026 Outlook, 2026-2033\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"India AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\nAustralia AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\nSouth Korea AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\nLatin America AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\nBrazil AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\nMEA AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\nSouth Africa AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\nSaudi Arabia AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\nUAE AI Agents Market Outlook\\\\n\\\\n## U.S. ai agents market highlights\\\\n\\\\n The U.S. ai agents market generated a revenue of USD 2,229.3 billio